{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775813366391,"sessionID":"ses_28948eb46ffeUQhCBpppPNpJ6U","part":{"id":"prt_d76b734b5001csBT7azC1zXmSG","messageID":"msg_d76b720820017ix1Nza5guZNz9","sessionID":"ses_28948eb46ffeUQhCBpppPNpJ6U","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_23b32068c5094d9d801a15af","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore project structure","prompt":"Explore the directory /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (list all directories and key files)\n2. Any existing Go code, especially in pkg/ directories\n3. Any existing design.md or documentation files\n4. Any existing HTTP service patterns or frameworks used in the project\n5. The go.mod file to understand dependencies\n6. Any existing workload manager related code\n7. Test patterns used in the project\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of the project structure, existing patterns, and any relevant code conventions.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28948be63ffeoU8zgWVLMGRQr6 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a complete picture of the project. Here is the comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary: AgentCube\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── .sdd_prompt.md              # SDD (Spec-Driven Development) prompt for AR-004\n├── coverage.out                # Go test coverage output\n├── delta-spec.md               # Gherkin-style requirements spec for AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP)\n├── design.md                   # Top-level design doc (AR-003: CRD shared types & constants)\n├── go.mod                      # Go module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube (Go 1.24.4)\n├── go.sum                      # Dependency checksums\n├── project.md                  # Project context overview\n├── test_spec.md                # TDD test case specification (12 test cases across 5 modules)\n│\n├── changes/                    # Change Request (AR) tracking\n│   ├── AR-001/                 # CRD AgentRuntime type definition (COMPLETED)\n│   ├── AR-002/                 # CRD CodeInterpreter type definition (COMPLETED)\n│   ├── AR-003/                 # CRD shared types & constants (COMPLETED)\n│   └── AR-004/                 # WorkloadManager HTTP service framework (IN PROGRESS - ST-1)\n│\n├── pkg/                        # Go source packages\n│   └── apis/\n│       └── runtime/\n│           └── v1alpha1/       # Kubernetes CRD type definitions (12 Go files)\n│\n├── cli-toolkit/                # Python CLI design + spec\n├── code-execution/             # PicoD code execution engine design + spec\n├── ci-cd/                      # CI/CD pipeline design + spec\n├── deployment/                 # Helm chart, Dockerfiles, Makefile, RBAC design + spec\n├── idle-cleanup/               # Agentd idle cleanup design + spec\n├── integrations/               # Dify plugin + PCAP analyzer example design + spec\n├── python-sdk/                 # Python SDK design + spec\n├── sandbox-orchestration/      # Core orchestration design + spec\n├── session-routing/            # Router (Gin-based reverse proxy) design + spec\n├── session-store/              # Redis/Valkey session store design + spec\n└── testing/\n    └── agentcube_tdd_manifest.md  # TDD manifest with test contracts per module\n```\n\n### 2. Existing Go Code (pkg/ directories)\n\nAll Go code lives in **`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`** -- there is **no other Go source code** in the project yet. The workloadmanager (`pkg/workloadmanager/`) does not exist yet (it is the target of AR-004).\n\n**Files in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` (12 files):**\n\n| File | Purpose | Lines |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `doc.go` | Package doc + k8s codegen markers (`+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package`, `+groupName`) | 3 |\n| `groupversion_info.go` | GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder, AddToScheme, Kind constants, Resource() helper | 33 |\n| `shared_types.go` | Shared types: `ProtocolType`, `AuthModeType`, `TargetPort` | 22 |\n| `constants.go` | Shared constants: `AnnotationKeyRuntime`, `AnnotationKeyVersion` | 6 |\n| `agent_type.go` | `AgentRuntime` CRD: `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `SandboxTemplate`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, `AgentRuntimeList` | 51 |\n| `codeinterpreter_types.go` | `CodeInterpreter` CRD: `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterList` | 61 |\n| `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated DeepCopy methods for all types | 324 |\n| `*_test.go` (5 files) | Unit tests using `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert` | ~1067 |\n\n**Key CRD Types:**\n- **API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- **AgentRuntime:** Generic AI agent sandbox, embeds `corev1.PodSpec` via `SandboxTemplate`\n- **CodeInterpreter:** Code-specific sandbox with flat `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` (image, command, args, resources, etc.), plus `WarmPoolSize` and `AuthMode` fields\n\n### 3. Existing Design and Documentation Files\n\n**Top-level docs:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md` -- Project overview, architecture diagram, tech stack table\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` -- AR-003 design (shared types extraction)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` -- Gherkin scenarios for AR-004\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test_spec.md` -- 12 test cases across 5 modules\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md` -- SDD prompt with full client-go generated code reference\n\n**Per-subsystem design + spec pairs (each has `design.md` and `spec.md`):**\n- `cli-toolkit/` -- Python CLI (Typer) with commands: pack, build, publish, invoke, status\n- `code-execution/` -- PicoD execution engine (Gin, JWT RS256 auth, file operations)\n- `ci-cd/` -- CI/CD pipeline design\n- `deployment/` -- Helm chart, Dockerfiles, Makefile targets, RBAC rules\n- `idle-cleanup/` -- Agentd idle cleanup controller\n- `integrations/` -- Dify plugin + PCAP analyzer FastAPI example\n- `python-sdk/` -- Python SDK design\n- `sandbox-orchestration/` -- Core orchestration design\n- `session-routing/` -- Router (Gin reverse proxy, JWT, concurrency limiting)\n- `session-store/` -- Redis/Valkey store with `Store` interface\n\n**Change request docs (each has `proposal.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md`, optionally `delta-spec.md`):**\n- `changes/AR-001/` -- AgentRuntime CRD type definition (completed)\n- `changes/AR-002/` -- CodeInterpreter CRD type definition (completed)\n- `changes/AR-003/` -- Shared types & constants (completed)\n- `changes/AR-004/` -- WorkloadManager HTTP service framework (in progress, design.md is mostly TODO placeholders)\n\n### 4. HTTP Service Patterns and Frameworks\n\nThe project consistently uses **Gin** (`github.com/gin-gonic/gin`) as the HTTP framework across all Go services:\n\n**Router (`session-routing/design.md`):**\n- `gin.New()` with `gin.Logger()` and `gin.Recovery()` global middleware\n- Route pattern: `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`\n- JWT RS256 auth middleware\n- Concurrency limiting middleware (buffered channel, returns 429)\n- `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy` for reverse proxying\n- Health endpoints: `/health/live`, `/health/ready`\n\n**PicoD (`code-execution/design.md`):**\n- `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)`, `gin.New()`, global `gin.Logger()` + `gin.Recovery()`\n- API group: `/api` with JWT auth middleware\n- Routes: `POST /api/execute`, `POST /api/files`, `GET /api/files`, `GET /api/files/*path`\n- Health: `GET /health`\n- `http.Server` with `ReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second`\n\n**WorkloadManager (AR-004 proposal -- not yet implemented):**\n- Planned to use Gin (chosen for consistency with Router)\n- Proposed routes: `/health`, `/v1/agent-runtime`, `/v1/code-interpreter`\n- Proposed `Server` struct with `*gin.Engine`, `*http.Server`, `clientset.Interface`\n- Middleware: `gin.Logger`, `gin.Recovery`, request ID tracking\n- Error format: `{\"error\": \"message\", \"code\": int}`\n\n**Python services:**\n- CLI uses **Typer** (`typer[all]>=0.9.0`)\n- PCAP analyzer example uses **FastAPI** (`fastapi==0.120.0`)\n\n### 5. go.mod Dependencies\n\n```\nModule: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\nGo: 1.24.4\n\nDirect dependencies:\n  github.com/stretchr/testify  v1.11.1     -- Testing (assert/require)\n  k8s.io/api                   v0.34.1     -- Kubernetes API types (corev1, etc.)\n  k8s.io/apimachinery          v0.34.1     -- metav1, runtime, schema, etc.\n  sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.22.2   -- scheme.Builder for CRD registration\n\nKey indirect dependencies:\n  github.com/go-logr/logr      v1.4.2      -- Structured logging\n  k8s.io/klog/v2               v2.130.1    -- Kubernetes logging\n  gopkg.in/yaml.v3             v3.0.1      -- YAML parsing\n  sigs.k8s.io/structured-merge-diff/v6 v6.3.0\n```\n\n**Notable: `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` is NOT yet in go.mod** -- it is planned for AR-004. The design docs for Router and PicoD reference Gin, but those packages do not yet exist in this working directory.\n\n### 6. Existing Workload Manager Related Code\n\n**There is NO existing workload manager implementation code.** The `pkg/workloadmanager/` directory does not exist. However, there is extensive design and specification work:\n\n- **`changes/AR-004/proposal.md`** (185 lines) -- Full proposal with scope, service structure, impact analysis, alternative evaluation (Gin chosen over stdlib/Echo/chi/controller-runtime), and 12 acceptance criteria\n- **`changes/AR-004/design.md`** (40 lines) -- Skeleton design doc with TODO placeholders\n- **`changes/AR-004/tasks.md`** (31 lines) -- Task checklist (mostly TODO)\n- **`delta-spec.md`** (227 lines) -- Gherkin BDD scenarios for 6 requirements:\n  - REQ-001: HTTP Server initialization and lifecycle (graceful shutdown, port conflict)\n  - REQ-002: AgentRuntime CRUD API (POST/GET/PUT/DELETE)\n  - REQ-003: CodeInterpreter CRUD API (POST/GET/PUT/DELETE)\n  - REQ-004: Request validation and error handling\n  - REQ-005: Health check endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`)\n  - REQ-006: Informer cache integration (SharedInformerFactory, cached reads, direct API writes)\n\n- **`.sdd_prompt.md`** (256 lines) -- Contains the complete generated client-go API reference (Clientset, Typed clients, Informers, Listers, Fake clients) that the WorkloadManager will consume\n\n**Planned WorkloadManager architecture (from AR-004 proposal):**\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── server.go              # Server struct, NewServer(), Run(), Shutdown()\n├── config.go              # Config struct (Port, KubeConfig, Debug)\n├── routes.go              # Route registration\n├── handler/\n│   ├── health.go\n│   ├── agent_runtime.go\n│   └── code_interpreter.go\n├── middleware/\n│   ├── logger.go\n│   └── recovery.go\n├── response/\n│   └── response.go        # Unified JSON response helper\n└── *_test.go files\n```\n\n### 7. Test Patterns Used in the Project\n\n**Go testing conventions:**\n\n| Pattern | Details |\n|---------|---------|\n| **Framework** | `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert` exclusively |\n| **File naming** | `*_test.go` co-located with source files (same package) |\n| **Test function naming** | `Test<Type><Scenario>` (e.g., `TestAgentRuntimeDeepCopy`, `TestCodeInterpreterSpecDefaults`) |\n| **Test categories** | Default/zero-value tests, DeepCopy isolation tests, Scheme registration tests, Constant value tests, All-fields tests, Nil-field handling tests |\n| **Helper functions** | `ptrInt32(i int32) *int32`, `parseQuantity(s string) resource.Quantity` defined in test files |\n| **DeepCopy testing pattern** | Create original -> `cp := original.DeepCopy()` -> assert equality -> modify copy -> assert original unchanged |\n| **Scheme testing pattern** | `runtime.NewScheme()` -> `AddToScheme(scheme)` -> `scheme.New(gvk)` -> `assert.IsType` |\n| **T/C Ratio requirement** | > 0.4 (per `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`) |\n| **Test execution** | `go test ./pkg/apis/... -v`, `go test ./... -coverprofile=coverage.out` |\n\n**Test file inventory (5 test files, ~1067 lines total):**\n\n| File | Lines | Key Tests |\n|------|-------|-----------|\n| `codeinterpreter_types_test.go` | 654 | Spec defaults, SandboxTemplate DeepCopy, CodeInterpreter DeepCopy, List DeepCopy, Status conditions, WarmPoolSize, AuthMode, Resources, RuntimeClassName, Environment, ImagePullSecrets |\n| `agent_type_test.go` | 235 | Default values, DeepCopy (full + isolation), List DeepCopy, SandboxTemplate DeepCopy, Spec DeepCopy, Status DeepCopy, nil template, empty ports, all-fields |\n| `shared_types_test.go` | 77 | ProtocolType constants, AuthModeType constants, TargetPort defaults/all-fields/DeepCopy, string representation |\n| `constants_test.go` | 21 | Annotation key values, non-empty, distinct |\n| `groupversion_info_test.go` | 80 | Scheme registration (both CRDs), GroupVersion constants, Resource helper, CodeInterpreter GVK constants, SchemeGroupVersion alias |\n\n**Python testing conventions (from design docs, not yet implemented):**\n- `pytest` with `pytest-asyncio`, `pytest-cov`, `pytest-mock`, `httpx-mock`\n- Test files: `test_*.py` or in `tests/` directory\n- T/C ratio > 0.4 required\n\n---\n\nThis is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform (AgentCube) under the `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` module. The project follows a Spec-Driven Development (SDD) methodology with formal change requests (AR-xxx). The CRD type definitions (AR-001 through AR-003) are complete and well-tested. The next major work item is AR-004: building the WorkloadManager HTTP service using Gin, which will serve as the control-plane API for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter sandbox lifecycles.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28948be63ffeoU8zgWVLMGRQr6","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore project structure","time":{"start":1775813214616,"end":1775813366387}}}}
